+# This is a simplified approach to structuring the workspace
+
+## The Chroma Rust Codebase Refactoring Plan
+
+To adhere to the workflow while focusing on what exactly needs to be accomplished, we will:
+
+1. Update the workspace Cargo.toml to include all necessary crates
+2. Establish a working crate structure that reflects the logical separation
+3. Ensure the essential "worker" crate dependencies are kept the same for functionality
+
+The main logical components needed are:
+- core crate (contains shared logic)
+- error definitions
+- types
+- config handling
+- Each major logical subsystem as a separate crate"
+
+## Workspace Structure
+
+The Cargo.toml in the root directory already lists the necessary member crates. The main crate that will be most affected is the worker crate which will now be more modularized.
